{
  "rule": "centered_2nd_uniform_latlon",
  "metric": "Linf",
  "expected_min_order": 1.9,
  "notes": "Centered 2nd-order FD on a uniform lat-lon grid is theoretically O(h^2) on the lat axis (the lon axis is exact for Y_{2,0} since the solution is lon-independent, ∂_lon Y_{2,0} ≡ 0). We require observed min order >= 1.9 across the n=16->32->64->128 sequence to tolerate minor pre-asymptotic drift. The harness drives the per-cell `cos_lat` and scalar `R`/`dlon`/`dlat` bindings through `apply_stencil_2d_latlon`; interior cells (lat boundaries excluded) supply the L_inf measurement."
}
